FCMB Group Plc has announced its financial results for the year ended December 31, 2021, which has seen the lender declare a higher dividend of 20 Kobo per share to shareholders compared to 15 Kobo per share in 2020. The result across market fundamentals shows an increased gross revenue to N212billion, representing a 7% growth compared to N198.4 billion in 2020. Also, a profit before tax of N22.7billion from N21.9billion the prior year while profit after tax also rose by 7% to N20.9 billion. 